---
title: Curry-Spiced Chicken with Lemony Yogurt plus Golden Raisin Rice & Pickled Cabbage
description: Sometimes you just need a little curry to spice up your week—and for those times, our chefs have your back. Tonight, they spiced up not one, not two, but THREE parts of this meal with curry spices: curried chicken, curry rice with golden raisins, and lemon curry sauce. Together with pickled red cabbage, these curried chicken bowls pack flavor into every bite.

image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/66955866b0a47382be870272-adbcc6d7.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/66f1e8f41e86f3e65846ecb7-en-US.pdf
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
servings: 2
cuisine: Indian
author: Michelle Doll Olson
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 22 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 69 g
  sugar: 21 g
  protein: 38 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 820 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/curry-spiced-chicken-with-lemony-yogurt-66f1e8f41e86f3e65846ecb7
---

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add
@curry powder{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4 servings); cook, stirring, until fragrant,
~{30%seconds} (you'll use more curry powder later).

Stir in @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, half the @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4), and @salt{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4). Bring to a boil,
then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, wash and dry produce.

Zest and quarter @lemon{1} (for 4 servings, zest one lemon and quarter both).
Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}.

In a #medium microwave-safe bowl{}, combine juice from half the lemon,
@water{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings), and @sugar{2%tsp} (4 tsp for 4). Stir in
@shredded red cabbage{4%oz}; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Microwave for
~{1%minute}. Add juice from remaining lemon and a big pinch of salt. Set aside
to pickle, stirring occasionally, until ready to serve.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, @yogurt{2%tbsp},
@curry powder{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4), and a pinch of lemon zest to taste (you'll
use the rest of the curry powder in the next step). Season with salt. Stir in
@water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
salt, pepper, and remaining @curry powder{3/4%tsp}.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165º.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook
until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. TIP: If chicken begins
to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium.

During the last minute of cooking, reduce heat to medium and stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) and remaining @chicken stock concentrate{1} until
melted and combined. Spoon butter mixture over chicken to coat.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @golden raisins{1%oz}, @butter{1/2%tbsp} (1 TBSP for 4 servings), @salt{1/4%tsp} (1/2 tsp for 4), and remaining lemon zest to
taste.

Drain cabbage; stir in half the cilantro.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with chicken and cabbage. Drizzle chicken with
sauce and garnish with remaining cilantro. Serve.